modules.description: Provides functions to parse and generate INI file content, including reading key-value pairs and sections, and writing structured data back to file format. Operates on strings and associative lists representing sections and their entries. Used to load configuration settings from disk and save application state persistently.

Processes INI file content by tokenizing input using predefined lexical tables. Operates on lexing buffers and returns custom token types representing sections, keys, and values. Used to parse configuration files by scanning through lines and identifying syntactic elements during initialization.

Parses INI files by scanning lexemes and constructing a list of sections, each containing key-value pairs. It processes lexing buffers and recognizes tokens to build a structured representation of configuration data. Used to load and interpret configuration files in applications requiring key-value sectioning.
